      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sensation of permanent loss and feeling like an unfeeling \"hollow shell\" is incredibly painful, often signaling a deep depression or existential crisis rather than just a temporary transition. Since you feel the previous \"you\" is gone forever, it might feel impossible to grieve what you can't, yet your pain is real even if the past version of you is no longer here. Please consider reaching out to a mental health professional who can help you navigate this profound sense of being cut off from your own life.",
